# More info: https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/builder/#dockerignore-file
# Ignore everything by default and re-include only needed files
**

# Re-include Go source files (but not *_test.go)
!**/*.go
**/*_test.go

# Re-include Go module files
!go.mod
!go.sum

# Re-include the vendored dependency tree wholesale. The build runs in
# -mod=vendor mode, which needs more than the *.go files re-included above:
# vendor/modules.txt (consistency manifest) plus non-Go build inputs such as
# assembly (*.s) and cgo sources. Dropping any of these breaks the build with
# "inconsistent vendoring". Listed last so it wins over the *_test.go exclusion.
!vendor
!vendor/**
